Description: Secure Boot chain watchdog with GNOME notifications
 secureboot-watchdog detects degradation of the Secure Boot chain on
 systemd-boot machines (unsigned DKMS modules, missing MOK enrollment,
 SBAT revocations, unsigned EFI binaries, TPM PCR drift) and offers a
 polkit-elevated one-click fix from a native GNOME notification.
 .
 It runs as a system oneshot service driven by a timer, a watcher on
 /var/lib/dkms, and a kernel postinst hook. A per-user path unit
 watches the resulting status file and pops a notification with an
 action button when something needs repair.
